      • generateThumbnailsAndPNGForImage

        public void generateThumbnailsAndPNGForImage(java.io.File imagePath,
                                    java.lang.String thumbnailW,
                                    java.lang.String thumbnailH)
                                      throws DCMAApplicationException
        Generates thumbnail and corresponding PNG for the image passed as parameter.

        These generated images are used to display images on UI. No information is lossed when images are converted to PNG format but size of images would be large.

        Parameters:
        imagePath - String path of image whose thumbnails and image needs to be generated.
        thumbnailW - String width of thumbnail image.
        thumbnailH - String height of thumbnail image.
        Throws:
        DCMAApplicationException - if unable to generate images for the given file.

      • generateThumbnailsAndJPGForImage

        public void generateThumbnailsAndJPGForImage(java.io.File imagePath,
                                    java.lang.String thumbnailW,
                                    java.lang.String thumbnailH)
                                      throws DCMAApplicationException
        Generates thumbnail and corresponding JPG for the image passed as parameter.

        These generated images are used to display images on UI. Thus jpeg images takes less memory in comparison to other type images. The images may loose some information as they are converted to jpeg.

        Parameters:
        imagePath - String path of image whose thumbnails and image needs to be generated.
        thumbnailW - String width of thumbnail image.
        thumbnailH - String height of thumbnail image.
        Throws:
        DCMAApplicationException - if unable to generate images for the given file.
